author: Ted Berg
title: Fox jumps the gun, advertises Royals-Mets World Series before ALCS is over
text:
Fox jumps the gun, advertises Royals-Mets World Series before ALCS is over USA Today Sports 10 hrs ago Ted Berg With the Royals holding a lead in the late innings of ALCS Game 6 on Friday, Fox aired a graphic advertising the Royals-Mets World Series matchup starting Tuesday.
AdChoices FOX calling this one early. pic.twitter.com/rcQQnlqIbu
â€” Paul Sporer (@sporer) October 24, 2015
One big issue? The Royals held that lead against the Blue Jays, and the Blue Jays have an unbelievable lineup that makes one- and two-run deficits look trivial. And sure enough, in the top of the eighth, Jose Bautista tied the game with another massive and triumphant home run.
Play-by-play man Joe Buck later acknowledged the error, calling it an accident and suggesting that the broadcast meant to show an ad for the Blue Jays-Royals Game 7 matchup that would've been played Saturday, if necessary.
